 How to use the `docker` command to run a Docker container
=====================================================

In this guide, we will cover how to use the `docker` command to run a Docker container. We will go over the basic syntax and options available for running a container.

Basic Syntax
-------------

The basic syntax for running a Docker container using the `docker` command is as follows:
```
docker run [OPTIONS] IMAGE [COMMAND]
```
Here's a breakdown of each part of the syntax:

* `docker run`: This is the command used to run a Docker container.
* `[OPTIONS]`: This is an optional parameter that allows you to specify additional options for the container.
* `IMAGE`: This is the name or ID of the Docker image you want to run.
* `[COMMAND]`: This is the command you want to run inside the container.

